title: Health impacts
comment: it is unclear what the long term health impacts would be - the technology feels untested

title: Productivity
comment: Improved productivity may lead to increased economic and social propperity

title: Academic achievement
comment: those with access could benefit academically and progress socially and economically - but is this a form of cheating?

title: Military
comment: improved military performance may result - but what are the health impacts on military personnel?

title: Improved sleep
comment: ability to manage sleep could lead to health and productivity benefits

title: Misuse
comment: in the wrong hands this implant could be used wrongfully

title: Inequity
comment: could create a new form of social inequality - those who can and cannot afford to benefit

title: Loss of control
comment: you would be partly controlled by an app and not in full control of your own actions

title: Hacking
comment: implant is controlled via a mobile app leaving it susceptible to attack in the wrong hands
